0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 22 "4.  Prime Numbe
rs.  A " }{TEXT 281 12 "prime number" }{TEXT -1 38 " is an integer (gr
eater than 1 -- why " }{TEXT 258 12 "greater than" }{TEXT -1 124 " 1?)
 for which the only (positive integer) factors are 1 and itself.  Exam
ples of prime numbers are: 2, 13, 101, 20110771.  " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 18 "The Maple command " }
{TEXT 259 7 "isprime" }{TEXT -1 58 " determines whether or not a given
 integer is prime.  Use " }{TEXT 260 7 "isprime" }{TEXT -1 105 " it to
 determine whether  the following numbers are prime:  29,  35,  1537, \+
 your ss#,   10!+1,  329891. " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 12 "isprime(29);" }}{PARA 11 "" 
1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#%%trueG" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 
