" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 3 "6. " }{TEXT 267 33 "Fundamental Theore
m of Arithmetic" }{TEXT -1 148 ".  The Fundamental Theorem of Arithmet
ic states that every integer can be factored in a unique way into a pr
oduct of powers of primes.  For example:" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 
1 " " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 5 "84 = " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "``(2)^2*``(
3)*``(7);" "6#*(-%!G6#\"\"#F'-F%6#\"\"$\"\"\"-F%6#\"\"(F+" }{TEXT -1 
4 " ;  " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 9 "28490 =  " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "``(2
)*``(5)*``(7)*``(11)*``(37);" "6#*,-%!G6#\"\"#\"\"\"-F%6#\"\"&F(-F%6#
\"\"(F(-F%6#\"#6F(-F%6#\"#PF(" }{TEXT -1 4 " ;  " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 21 "5813258142483000  =  " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "``(2)^3*``(3)^4*``
(5)^3*``(11)^2*``(23)^3*``(29)*``(41)^2;" "6#*0-%!G6#\"\"#\"\"$-F%6#F(
\"\"%-F%6#\"\"&F(-F%6#\"#6F'-F%6#\"#BF(-F%6#\"#H\"\"\"-F%6#\"#TF'" }
{TEXT -1 4 " .  " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 17 "It is called the " }{TEXT 270 11 "Fundamental" }{TEXT -1 
217 " Theorem of Arithmetic because of the role it plays in both simpl
e and deep results in algebra and number theory.  There are numerous a
nd important facts which follow because of  the Fundamental Theorem of
 Arithmetic." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 10 "          " }}{PARA 0 "" 
0 "" {TEXT -1 111 "Use paper and pencil to factor the following intege
rs into their prime decompositions:  340340, 38*865, 10!.   " }}{PARA 
0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 266 16 "Answers:  kp ?
??" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 19 "The
 Maple command  " }{TEXT 268 7 "ifactor" }{TEXT -1 32 " does this auto
matically.   Use " }{TEXT 269 7 "ifactor" }{TEXT -1 102 " to verify yo
ur results from above.  Now factor the following numbers:  384*8650,  \+
10!+1 ,  your ss#. " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 
"> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 16 "ifactor(340340);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" 
