{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#/\"-+S/YNt*,)-%!G6#\"\"#\"\"&\"\"\")-F
(6#\"\"$\"\"*F,)-F(6#F+F0F,-F(6#\"\"(F,)-F(6#\"#6F0F," }}}{PARA 0 "" 
0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 11 "You assign " }{TEXT 
272 2 "x " }{TEXT -1 4 "and " }{TEXT 273 1 "y" }{TEXT -1 88 " to be an
y pair of numbers (positive integers).  Execute the following command \+
sequence:" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 14 "x :=3;\ny := 4;
" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%\"xG\"\"$" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" 
{XPPMATH 20 "6#>%\"yG\"\"%" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 
27 "x=ifactor(x);\ny=ifactor(y);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#/
\"\"$-%!G6#F$" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#/\"\"%*$)-%!G6#\"\"#F
*\"\"\"" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 17 "x*y=ifactor(x*y)
;" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#/\"#7*&)-%!G6#\"\"#F*\"\"\"-F(6#
\"\"$F+" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 27 "gcd(x,y)=ifactor
(gcd(x,y));" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#/\"\"\"F$" }}}{EXCHG 
{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 27 "lcm(x,y)=ifactor(lcm(x,y));" }}
{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#/\"#7*&)-%!G6#\"\"#F*\"\"\"-F(6#\"\"$F
+" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 45 "lcm(x,y)*gcd(x,y)=ifac
tor(lcm(x,y)*gcd(x,y));" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#/\"#7*&)-%!
G6#\"\"#F*\"\"\"-F(6#\"\"$F+" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }{TEXT 271 104 "What was the common them
e of the above three sets of calculations for different pairs of numbe
rs?  kp ??" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
-1 147 "Use the Fundamental Theorem of Arithmetic to provide a written
 argument to verify the general formula that for any pair of positive \+
integers (m,n):" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 34 "         mn = gcd(m,n) * lcm(m,n)." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 274 140 "Argument: The gcd is a \+
common factor or prime from both numbers. The gcd is then multiplied b
y the LCMs to get the original mn.   kp - why??" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 198 "8.   Numerical Approxima
tions.  While Maple can perform exact arithmetic, there are times when
 it is important or helpful to obtain a decimal approximation for some
 exact answer.  For instance, the " }{TEXT 275 5 "solve" }{TEXT -1 66 
" command can be used to find the \"exact\" roots of the polynomial  \+
" }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "p := x^3-11*x^2-70*x+600;" "6#>%\"pG,**$%\"xG\"\"$\"
\"\"*&\"#6F)*$F'\"\"#F)!\"\"*&\"#qF)F'F)F.\"$+'F)" }{TEXT -1 38 " .  E
xecute the following command:    " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 50 "x:='x':roots_of_p := solve(x
^3-11*x^2-70*x+600,x);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%+roots_of_
pG6%\"\"',&#\"\"&\"\"#\"\"\"*(F)F+F*!\"\"\"#<#F+F*F+,&F(F+*(F)F+F*F-F.
F/F-" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 289 
"That isn't very illuminating.  It maybe hard to tell, but there are t
hree roots.  If you change the problem slightly, it may be even harder
.  (For example, change the number 70 in the above problem to 80 and t
hen do the calculation!)  To display each root separately, execute the
 commands:" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "
" {MPLTEXT 1 0 50 "x:='x':roots_of_p := solve(x^3-11*x^2-80*x+600,x);
" }}{PARA 12 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%+roots_of_pG6%,(*&\"\"$!\"\",&\"
%4GF)*&^#\"#!*\"\"\"\"%M[#F/\"\"#F/#F/F(F/*(\"$h$F/F(F)F*#F)F(F/#\"#6F
(F/,**&\"\"'F)F*F3F)*(F5F/F;F)F*F6F)F7F/*(^#F1F/F(F1,&*&F(F)F*F3F/*(F5
F/F(F)F*F6F)F/F/,**&F;F)F*F3F)*(F5F/F;F)F*F6F)F7F/*(^##F)F2F/F(F1F?F/F
/" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 24 "r1 := Re(roots_of_p[1]
);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%#r1G,&#\"#6\"\"$\"\"\"*&#F)F(F
)-%#ReG6#,&*$),&\"%4G!\"\"*&^#\"#!*F)\"%M[#F)\"\"#F)F+F)F)*&\"$h$F)F2#
F4F(F)F)F)" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 24 "r2 := Re(root
s_of_p[2]);" }}{PARA 12 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%#r2G,&#\"#6\"\"$\"\"
\"*&#F)\"\"'F)-%#ReG6#,(*$),&\"%4G!\"\"*&^#\"#!*F)\"%M[#F)\"\"#F)#F)F(
F)F5*&\"$h$F)F3#F5F(F5*(^#F(F)F(F:,&*&F(F5F3F<F)*(F>F)F(F5F3F?F5F)F)F)
F)" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 24 "r3 := Re(roots_of_p[3
]);" }}{PARA 12 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%#r3G,&#\"#6\"\"$\"\"\"*&#F)\"
\"'F)-%#ReG6#,(*$),&\"%4G!\"\"*&^#\"#!*F)\"%M[#F)\"\"#F)#F)F(F)F5*&\"$
h$F)F3#F5F(F5*(^#!\"$F)F(F:,&*&F(F5F3F<F)*(F>F)F(F5F3F?F5F)F)F)F)" }}}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 47 "Even that
 isn't all that helpful.  The command " }{TEXT 276 5 "evalf" }{TEXT 
-1 187 "  which stands for \"evaluate using floating point\" can be us
ed to give a decimal approximation of an value.  The number of decimal
 places can be specified.  Execute the following command:" }}{PARA 0 "
" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 10 "evalf
(r1);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#$\"+<j,k8!\")" }}}{EXCHG 
{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 10 "evalf(r2);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" 
{XPPMATH 20 "6#$!+`T]#3)!\"*" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 
0 10 "evalf(r3);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#$\"+\")4MUa!\"*" }
}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 98 "With th
ese last computations,  we at least have a feel for the general locati
on of the roots of p." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 
"" {TEXT -1 199 "To obtain a feel for what \"floating point arithmetic
\" means, execute the following command sequence and record any releva
nt observations about what the commands do, automatic features of Mapl
e, etc. " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 1 " " }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" 
{MPLTEXT 1 0 6 "1+2/3;" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6##\"\"&\"\"$
" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 9 "evalf(%);" }}{PARA 11 "
" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#$\"+nmmm;!\"*" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" 
{MPLTEXT 1 0 12 "1/2+1/3+1/4;" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6##\"#8
\"#7" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 9 "evalf(%);" }}{PARA 
11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#$\"+LLL$3\"!\"*" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "
" {MPLTEXT 1 0 8 "2/(3*4);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6##\"\"\"
\"\"'" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 9 "evalf(%);" }}{PARA 
11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#$\"+nmmm;!#5" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" 
{MPLTEXT 1 0 9 "(7/3)^15;" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6##\".V*4:c
