{TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 257 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 386 "When the Digits value \+
was changed, the values of ans_exact and ans_approx were not changed. \+
 If they were not changed, then why are the values diff_10 and diff_10
0 different?  What is Maple doing different when Digits = 10 as compar
ed to Digits = 100, so that diff_10 and diff_100 are different?  (The \+
point of this question is to verbally clarify what floating point arit
hmetic means.)" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 161 "If the digi
ts are set at 10. Then no matter what two numbers you multiply togethe
r the answer will be given in 10 digits.The rest of the digits will no
t show up." }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
-1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 157 "If the digits are
 set at 100, then you will get an answer with 100 digits. After 100 th
en the digits will not show. Only 100 digits would show in the answer.
" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" 
{MPLTEXT 1 0 78 "!0 is different from 100 because 10 shows 10 digits, \+
and 100 shows 100 digits." }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 
